        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:48PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stonehouse Recreation Area, or 17 miles west of Danville, moving east
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stonehouse Recreation Area...     Gravelly...
Fourche Valley...                 Wing...
Waltreak...                       Bluffton...
Briggsville...                    Blue Ball...
Macedonia in Yell County...       Nola...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
